<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"falling">Falling</h3>



<p>The feeling of falling through the air while dreaming is a frequent them=
e that has emerged from dream research. Falling is a common sensation peopl=
e experience before a hypnic jerk.<a href=3D"https://www.sleepfoundation.or=
g/parasomnias/hypnic-jerks"> Hypnic jerks</a> are involuntary lurches that =
can involve a part of the body or the body as a whole.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"flying">Flying</h3>



<p>Freud believed that people dream about flying because of their childhood=
 memories of being thrown into the air or swung around. Research conducted =
in the 1970s found that flying dreams were connected to a desire for freedo=
m     <span class=3D"source-shortcode d-inline font-weight-normal" data-sou=
rce-index=3D"8">
        <span></span>
        <span class=3D"position-relative">
          =20
                            <span class=3D"smooth-scroll" data-id=3D"#refer=
ences-278574">
                    <a href=3D"https://www.sleepfoundation.org/dreams/dream=
-interpretation#references-278574" class=3D"source-domain" rel=3D"noopener =
nofollow">
                        <span class=3D"source-link position-relative source=
-text " data-source-id=3D"278574" data-source-index=3D"8">
                        </span>
                    </a>
                </span>
                    </span>
    </span>=20
    . Because flying dreams often involve vigorous physical activity, peopl=
e may be more likely to remember them than other types of dreams.</p>



